item.title: Poll: Clinton's edge over GOP gone

item.title: What your cat is really trying to say
item.description: Dogs we get, mostly because they are so easy to get. They have expressive faces and body language that we can read pretty accurately, according to researchers who study animal behavior. Cats, on the other hand, are known for their emotional opaqueness and standoffishness; even the cat-ladiest of cat ladies might think that their pets don't seem altogether interested in communicating with them, as long as the food arrives on time.
